alse,"pantry_items":["olive oil","kosher salt","black pepper"],"pantry_items_full":[{"name":"olive oil","quantity":"2.0","measurementUnit":"tablespoon","displayOrder":10,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/267/medium_square_olive-oil-test.jpg"},{"name":"kosher salt","quantity":null,"measurementUnit":"","displayOrder":11,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/473/medium_square_kosher-salt.jpg"},{"name":"black pepper","quantity":null,"measurementUnit":"","displayOrder":12,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/493/medium_square_spice-black-pepper-test.jpg"}],"steps":[{"title":"Prepare Ingredients","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/13242/recipe_card_size_1._Prepare_Ingredients.jpg","description":"Bring a large pot of water to a boil over high heat. Mince \u003cb\u003egarlic\u003c/b\u003e. Rinse \u003cb\u003etomatoes\u003c/b\u003e and halve. Rinse \u003cb\u003ebasil\u003c/b\u003e and set aside 1 whole sprig; roughly chop remaining leaves, discarding stems. "},{"title":"Sauté Tomatoes","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/13243/recipe_card_size_2._Saute_Tomatoes.jpg","description":"Heat \u003cb\u003e2 tablespoons olive oil\u003c/b\u003e in a large pan over medium heat. When oil is shimmering, add as much \u003cb\u003ecrushed red pepper\u003c/b\u003e as desired (it's spicy!) and \u003cb\u003egarlic\u003c/b\u003e and sauté, stirring, until fragrant, about 1 minute. Increase heat to medium-high and add \u003cb\u003etomatoes\u003c/b\u003e. Sauté, breaking up with a spoon, until beginning to soften, 4-5 minutes. Season with \u003cb\u003e.25 teaspoon salt\u003c/b\u003e and \u003cb\u003eblack pepper\u003c/b\u003e as desired."},{"title":"Simmer Tomato Sauce","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/13244/recipe_card_size_3._Simmer_Tomato_Sauce.jpg","description":"Add \u003cb\u003ewhite wine\u003c/b\u003e, \u003cb\u003etomato purée\u003c/b\u003e, and \u003cb\u003ewhole basil sprig\u003c/b\u003e to pan with tomatoes. Increase heat to high and bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium and simmer, stirring occasionally, until tomatoes are very tender, 1-2 minutes. Remove pan from heat."},{"title":"Cook Spaghetti","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/13240/recipe_card_size_4._Cook_Pasta.jpg","description":"Season boiling water generously with \u003cb\u003esalt\u003c/b\u003e. Stir in \u003cb\u003espaghetti\u003c/b\u003e and cook until al dente, about 3 minutes. Reserve \u003cb\u003e.5 cup pasta cooking water\u003c/b\u003e, then drain."},{"title":"Season Spaghetti","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/13241/recipe_card_size_5._Season_Pasta.jpg","description":"Remove and discard basil sprig from tomato sauce, then add \u003cb\u003espaghetti\u003c/b\u003e to pan over medium heat. Cook, stirring, until pasta is coated and warmed through, 1-2 minutes. Add \u003cb\u003ereserved pasta cooking water\u003c/b\u003e, 1 tablespoon at a time, until sauce is thick and clings to noodles (see Recipe Tip). Stir in \u003cb\u003epecorino\u003c/b\u003e. Taste and add more \u003cb\u003esalt\u003c/b\u003e and \u003cb\u003eblack pepper\u003c/b\u003e as needed."},{"title":"Plate Spaghetti ","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/13239/recipe_card_size_6._Plate_Pasta.jpg","description":"Divide \u003cb\u003espaghetti\u003c/b\u003e evenly between 2 plates. Remove \u003cb\u003eburrata\u003c/b\u003e from container, discarding excess liquid (see Recipe Tip). Tear into bite-size pieces and place over plated spaghetti. Garnish with \u003cb\u003echopped basil\u003c/b\u003e, grab a fork, and twirl away."}],"tags":{"all":[{"name":"vegetarian","slug":"vegetarian","hex_color":""},{"name":"Stovetop only","slug":"stovetop-only","hex_c